    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your<strong> basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-cod-with-coconut-curry-sauce-and-mustardy-greens/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong> then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-cod-with-coconut-curry-sauce-and-mustardy-greens/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut pieces of<strong> tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper and layer them over each other</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded kale </strong>to the middle with your <strong>black mustard seeds</strong>, a couple of small knobs of <strong>butter</strong> and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the greens to form 1 sealed parcel per person and add to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-14 min or until the greens are tender \u2013 these are your <strong>mustardy greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-cod-with-coconut-curry-sauce-and-mustardy-greens/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whist the greens are in the oven, add your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> to a separate <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 14-15 min or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-cod-with-coconut-curry-sauce-and-mustardy-greens/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>While the fish is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly softened, then add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-cod-with-coconut-curry-sauce-and-mustardy-greens/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>,<strong> chopped creamed coconut </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>in<strong> </strong>250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> curry powder</strong>, <strong>half </strong>of<strong> </strong>your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until everything is covered in the spices</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-cod-with-coconut-curry-sauce-and-mustardy-greens/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut</strong> <strong>curry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-cod-with-coconut-curry-sauce-and-mustardy-greens/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>baked cod </strong>over the <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> with the <strong>mustardy greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Pour the <strong>coconut</strong> <strong>curry sauce</strong> on the fish and tear your <strong>coriander</strong> over the top</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining dried chilli flakes</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
